==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hanukkah
<hw>Ha"nuk*kah</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Heb. <ets>khanukk⟦amac⟧h</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The Jewish Feast of the Dedication, instituted by Judas Maccabaeus,
his brothers, and the whole congregation of Israel, in 165 <sc>b.
c.</sc>, to commemorate the dedication of the new altar set up at the
purification of the temple of Jerusalem to replace the altar which had
been polluted by Antiochus Epiphanes of Syria (<au>1 Maccabees i. 58,
iv. 59</au>). The feast, which is mentioned in John x. 22, is held for
eight days (beginning with the 25th day of Kislev, corresponding to
December), and is celebrated everywhere, chiefly as a festival of
lights, by the Jews.</def> <altsp>[Also spelled
<asp>Chanuka</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Chanukah, Festival of Lights, Feast of Dedication,
Feast of the Dedication.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hanuman</ent>⟦br⟧
